## Who is in charge?

The absolute boss of the DOM is the **`window`** object.

When a tab opens in your browser, JavaScript creates a massive Global Object named `window` that represents that entire visual tab!

```javascript
// Everything we use is secretly attached to the window!
window.console.log("Hello!");

// Most people just leave the word window off!
console.log("This still works!");
```

The `window` tracks *everything*, from the screen width to the user's scroll depth!
